commit c7fcb5bb4590a3903ab4284dfbbdb50c4fb18333
Author: doctor-doom <doctor-doom@happylight.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 19 11:25:22 2026 +0900

    fix(anthropic): strip cloaked tool names on local-proxy responses
    
    Outbound build_anthropic_kwargs CamelCase-cloaks tool names for proxied
    endpoints (headroom/cliproxy via local.anthropic.com), but response
    normalization only stripped the prefix for OAuth. On a local proxy the
    Mcp* names came back uncloaked, breaking tool execution.
    
    - conversation_loop.py: gate strip_tool_prefix on
      _is_anthropic_oauth OR _use_cc_tool_cloak(base_url) at both the main
      (3601) and truncation (1708) normalize_response sites.
    - chat_completion_helpers.py: base_url falls back to agent.base_url
      when _anthropic_base_url is unset, so cloak detection sees the proxy.
    
    Verified: hermes -z 'Run terminal: echo TOOLCALL_WORKS' round-trips
    200 with no cliproxy third-party 400.

